From 3b1292d4905873f452a50ef6df6b634626fedd19 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Soumyadeep Hore <soumyadeep.hore@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 10:35:15 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] examples/txpp: add Tx packet pacing example

Add a new example application demonstrating E830 Tx Packet Pacing
(TxPP) with configurable intra-burst spacing. The application sends
bursts of packets with precise hardware-level timing using the TXTIME
offload and captures received packets with hardware RX timestamps.

Features:
  - Configurable intra-burst interval (128ns granularity)
  - Configurable inter-burst gap, burst size, packet size
  - Hardware PHC clock for scheduling future TX timestamps
  - Optional RX port with hardware timestamp capture
  - Nanosecond pcap output for validation
Signed-off-by: Soumyadeep Hore <soumyadeep.hore@intel.com>
